The study of trees and induced subgraphs suggests a focus on discrete mathematics, which is covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The connection to the Potts model suggests a focus on information theory, which is covered by cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the use of graph theory and approximation algorithms suggests a focus on graph theory, which is covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
